# Private neutralization markers — EXAMPLE / template.
#
# Copy this file to `neutralize-extra.txt` (gitignored) and fill it with YOUR OWN
# company / name markers. It is read by .github/check-neutralized.sh on local and
# pre-commit runs, so the public template stays neutral while you still catch your
# own identifiers before they reach a public repo.
#
# Format: one `grep -E` pattern per line. Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored.
# Keep your real copy in your PRIVATE vault — it must never be committed here.
#
# Examples (replace with your own, then delete these):
# your-company
# your-company\.(com|io|eu)
# \byour-first-name\b
# internal-tool-name
